ZH: 他经常对别人说谎。
EN: He often lies to others.

ZH: 她说谎就是为了炫耀。
EN: She lies just to show off.

ZH: 我们不能接受他的说谎行为。
EN: We cannot accept his habit of lying.

ZH: 他的说谎被很快揭穿了。
EN: His lie was quickly revealed.

ZH: 她的母亲感到失望，因为她经常说谎。
EN: Her mother was disappointed because she often tells lies.

ZH: 没有任何理由可以为说谎辩护。
EN: There is no justification for lying.

ZH: 他为了不让别人知道实情，只得说谎。
EN: He had to lie to hide the truth from others.

ZH: 听说她的儿子常常说谎。
EN: It is said that her son often tells lies.

ZH: 他为了逃避责任而不断说谎。
EN: He keeps lying to avoid responsibility.

ZH: 我们应该守诺言，不要说谎。
EN: We should keep our promises and not lie.

ZH: 我们必须保持诚实，不要说谎。
EN: We must maintain honesty and not lie.

ZH: 说谎是一种不负责任的行为。
EN: Lying is an irresponsible act.

ZH: 她说谎的理由完全站不住脚。
EN: Her reason for lying is completely groundless.

ZH: 不管原因如何，说谎是不对的。
EN: Regardless of the reason, lying is wrong.

ZH: 他承认自己以前说谎过。
EN: He admits to having lied in the past.

ZH: 说谎可能导致人际关系破裂。
EN: Lying can lead to the breakdown of relationships.

ZH: 我没有必要对你说谎。
EN: I have no reason to lie to you.

ZH: 你为什么总是对我说谎？
EN: Why do you always lie to me?

ZH: 他们的说谎让她感到非常伤心。
EN: Their lies made her very sad.

ZH: 你说谎的嘴巴会惹来麻烦。
EN: Your lying mouth will get you into trouble.

ZH: 我讨厌说谎的人。
EN: I dislike people who lie.
